        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "As a mortal you were gifted with The Sight and in 1970s San Diego you could actually make a living with such a real psychic gift.  In a sign of fate your visions drew the attention of the True Black Hand (TalMaHeRa/TMR).  The Rafastio Revenant family kidnapped you in San Diego and through secret artifice transported you to the Shadowlands where the Wraiths dwell.  There you were taken to Enoch in shadow and embraced by a seer who advised the Del-Roh himself.  Although you lost the gift when you became a vampire, the True Hand still had need of you.  After studying with the True Brujah loremaster Qusan for a decade you returned to the fleshlands and became a member of the False Hand.  As an infiltrator into the Camarilla you served the Black Hand, both True and False, and prepared for the final nights.  You had established yourself as an Elder in New York city when you heard of Enoch's fall and the destruction of the True Hand.  While you keep that identity, you've returned to San Diego as your Sabbat self in hopes of discovering the secret ways into the Shadowlands.  You've taken control of the Rafastio family here, but none who can cross the shroud survived the fall of Enoch."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Artemis Crane",
          "Reference: (If any)",
